§ 8. For cessio bonorum see p. 377 supr. Societas could be dissolved, besides the modes mentioned in the text, (1) by lapse of the time for which it was originally formed, Dig. 17. 2. 1. pr. 3 ib. 65. 6. Where per- sons had become partners for a definite term neither could withdraw during it except on a reasonable ground, Dig. ib. 14-16, in the absence of which it was open to the other to treat the partnership as still sub- sisting, ib. 65. 6; (2) By division, either voluntary and extrajudicial, or enforced through action by one of the socii: for the form of this see next note.
